2022-09-06  Nathan Potter  <ndp@opendap.org>
	    myang6  <myang6@hdfgroup.org>

	Dmrpp string arrays (#668)
	This commit includes the code in support of HYRAX-653 and includes:
	Code to detect fixed length string arrays and add the relevant information to the dmr++ by adding the element:
	<dmrpp:FixedLengthStringArray string_length="###" pad="null | space"/>
	Support for arrays of fixed length strings stored with either the Contiguous or Chunked layouts.
	Support for arrays of fixed length strings stored in the Compact layout is not yet supported. (But will be soon)
	Arrays of variable ;length strings are not yet supported.
	* Add string handling code/files.
	* Added simple Makefile for hdf5 dev code
	* Reviewed PODAACs array of string issues and made a notes.md file.
	* Add introduction to notes.md
	* CMakeLists, structured output from h5_obj_addr_info, retired redundant code
	* Added pad removal function
	* Simplifying loops ala c++11
	* resurrected read_str_vars.cc as read_str_vars_orig.cc from Kent's initial check-in
	* Fixed broken String reads
	* Comments
	* Trying to set up fixed length string state in build_dmrpp.cc
	* Identifying fixed length string arrays and apply appropriate state to DmrppArray and then using that state to produce a dmr++ file that contains said state.
	* misc cleanup
	* Updated baselines for FixLengthStringArray datasets
	* Dropping exception for unknown state.
	* Updating offset and size (ons) code
	* Simplified constructor defs
	* Syncing... DmrppMetadataTest still broken. Retired DmrppParserSax2
	* Cleaning up MDA mess
	* Fixed broken tests
	* Added read code for fixed length string arrays
	* Added first string array test (broken) and tests data files
	* Working for 1D arrays of fixed length strings
	* Add full dap test for arrays of fixed length strings
	* Added tests for contiguous array of fixed length strings
	* Added tests for contiguous, chunked, and ctsr style hdf5 strings
	* Fixing macro def for HEX
	* Removed unnecessary local variable
	* Fiddle dmrpp paths
	* Updating string array baselines
	* tests work except the chunked scalar variable is reporting too many chars
	* Fixed distcheck issue, still failing for scalar strings
	* I think I fixed a bug in DmrppStr in which the data were not being QC'd
	* Packed up thg dev code.
	* Update .gitignore [skip ci]

